<p>
<a name="do-and-return">@EM{{@Vte{{}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}}}</a> can mean to go somewhere, perform an action and return.
If necessary, the place where the remote action happens can be indicated by @HI{{de}}.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{chottotabakowo@KJ{{buy}}@EM{{tte@KJ{{come}}masu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I'm just popping out to buy some cigarettes.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

<p>
If the purpose is to go somewhere and move something, then @HI{{kara}} is used instead to indicate the place where the movement happens.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{pedestal^place}}kara@KT{{koppu}}wo @KJ{{take}}@EM{{tte @KJ{{come}}masu}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    I'm going to fetch a glass from the kitchen.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="process-start">@EM{{@Vte{{}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}}}</a> can indicate the beginning of a process when used with a verb
