  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    Now I have begun to understand computers.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="to-present">@EM{{@Vte{{}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}}}</a> can indicate the continuation of a process up to
the current point in time. This usage applies to any non-puntual verb.

<table class="sentence" border=0>
  <tr class="jp"> <td>
    @HI{{@KJ{{private}}hairoiro@KJ{{day^book}}no@KJ{{curriculum^history^write}}wo@KJ{{read}}@EM{{nde@KJ{{come}}mashita}}.}}
  </td> </tr>
  <tr class="en"> <td>
    Up to now I've been reading various Japanese histories.
  </td> </tr>
</table>
</p>

@BGRND{{}}
<p>
<a name="simple-and">@EM{{@Vte{{}}@KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}}}</a> can simply indicate "@Vte{{}} and then @KJ{{come}}@HI{{ru}}".

<table class="sentence" border=0>
